OL,3,CLyrid meteor shower: How and when to
OL,4,Cwatch 'shooting stars' peak
OL,6,FSpace is full of tiny bits of dust and
OL,7,Frock. When Earth travels around the
OL,8,Fsun, it sometimes passes through dusty
OL,9,Ftrails left behind by comets (a sort
OL,10,Fof frozen, crumbly clump of ice, dust
OL,11,Fand small bits of rock generally just
OL,12,Fa few kilometres wide).
OL,14,FAs the Earth moves through each cloud
OL,15,Fof space dust, the dust heats and
OL,16,Fburns up in our atmosphere, creating
OL,17,Flots of bright streaks in the sky.
OL,19,FThe flash of them burning up is what
OL,20,Fwe call a meteor or "shooting star".
OL,26,@|D@UOU|D@cO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
