OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1776801953
OL,3,CLyrid meteor shower: How and when to
OL,4,Cwatch 'shooting stars' peak
OL,6,FAncient Chinese astronomers documented
OL,7,Fthe shower as early as 687 BCE, noting
OL,8,Fthat "stars fell like rain".
OL,10,FLyrid meteors are particularly known
OL,11,Ffor their speed and brightness.
OL,13,FWhile many appear as quick flashes,
OL,14,Fsome leave behind glowing trails that
OL,15,Flinger for a few seconds.
OL,17,FOn rare occasions, the shower produces
OL,18,F"fireballs", which are exceptionally
OL,19,Fbright meteors that can briefly
OL,20,Filluminate the landscape.
OL,26,@pD@FOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
