OL,3,CLyrid meteor shower: How and when to
OL,4,Cwatch 'shooting stars' peak
OL,6,FHow often do they happen?
OL,8,FThe Lyrid meteor shower happens once a
OL,9,Fyear, but there are plenty of other
OL,10,Fmeteor showers if you miss these
OL,11,Ftonight.
OL,13,FThe Royal Observatory Greenwich lists
OL,14,Fseveral major showers every year:
OL,16,FWhere and when is best to see them?
OL,18,FThe Lyrid meteor shower runs from
OL,19,FApril 16 to 25 each year, but
OL,20,Ftypically peaks around April 21/22
OL,21,Fwith around 10-20 meteors per hour.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
