PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1776801953
OL,3,CLyrid meteor shower: How and when to
OL,4,Cwatch 'shooting stars' peak
OL,6,FThe best time to watch tends to be in
OL,7,Fthe early hours of the morning,
OL,8,Fbetween 2am and 4am.
OL,10,FIt's better to be under dark, clear
OL,11,Fskies, so try to get away from city
OL,12,Flights.
OL,14,FYou don't need any special equipment
OL,15,Fto watch the Lyrids, as binoculars or
OL,16,Ftelescopes can limit your field of
OL,17,Fview.
OL,19,FFor the best view, it's worth giving
OL,20,Fyour eyes around 20-30 minutes to
OL,21,Fadjust to the darkness.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
